snippet.textDisplay: Seriously... all of these are "dips" or "bends", or whatever you want to call them. Calling the motions in this video "squats" is like calling crunches "sit-ups". You're doing half (more like quarter) rep, and claiming to do the full thing. The difference is that properly executed crunches are basically as good as full sit-ups. Improperly executed squats just simply AREN'T SQUATS, they are some other type of motion. So congratulations on doing however many bends you did, or whatever. I'm not saying it wasn't difficult. I'm sure it was taxing.  I'm also saying they weren't SQUATS.
